''t draw attention, fitting for a character of this stratum.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Rusty Cooper", "rationale": "''Rusty'' as a nickname/first name suggests someone who is weathered, a bit rough, and perhaps not from a privileged background, aligning well with the connotations of ''麻子''. ''Cooper'' is a straightforward, occupational surname that feels authentic for a character in a small-town or rural setting.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}]', 0, '{"en-US": true, "ja-JP": true}', '{"en-US": "cultural_equivalent", "ja-JP": "cultural_equivalent"}');


