ming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Lan Bu Bao Fu", "rationale": "Retains the original Chinese term, which might be used for stylistic flavor or in a context where the specific cultural item is emphasized.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "a769281d8de44c91a2761ae276444d1a", "candidates": [{"name": "The Griddle Cake in the Oilpaper Wrapper", "rationale": "Precisely describes the food item and its packaging, important for period and sensory detail.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "The Oiled-Paper Parcel of Flatbread", "rationale": "Uses more familiar terms (''oiled-paper,'' ''flatbread'') for the materials and food, making the description flow naturally in English while keeping the essential idea.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Youzhibao li de Laobing", "rationale": "Preserves the original Chinese name, suitable for a heavily stylized or culturally immersive text.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "02c6ca68267e4cfebb74a10cc1e58530", "candidates": [{"name": "(The Implied) Ledger", "rationale": "Directly translates the key object (''ledger'') and includes the narrative note ''implied'' in parentheses, as per the original.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "The Ledger", "rationale": "Uses the standard English term for a record-keeping book. The ''implied'' nature would be conveyed through context in the narrative, not the name itself.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Zhangben (Yinhan)", "rationale": "Provides the Chinese term with a transliterated note. This is less common for props but could be used for specific stylistic effect.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "4c9f5b9ef57a49e6a456bdec2f9dc8ce", "candidates": [{"name": "Suspense", "rationale": "The direct and standard translation for the genre/style ''悬疑''.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "Mystery/Thriller", "rationale": "Uses common English genre labels that closely match the connotations of ''悬疑'', often encompassing both mystery and thriller elements.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Xuanyi", "rationale": "Retains the Chinese genre term, which could be used in a meta-context about story styles or for a specialized audience.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "b5a3fa41e70a4d09bbdfa7b6b05f05b3", "candidates": [{"name": "Plot", "rationale": "The direct and accurate translation for ''剧情'' as a narrative style focus.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "Story-Driven", "rationale": "A common English phrase used to describe a narrative that emphasizes plot and character development over other elements.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Juqing", "rationale": "The transliterated term, less common for style descriptors but possible in certain contexts.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "cd0aaef3eedb4e05a681c76a31daf8ea", "candidates": [{"name": "Period", "rationale": "A direct translation capturing the idea of a story set in a specific historical era.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "Historical / Period Piece", "rationale": "Common English terms for narratives defined by their historical setting. ''Period Piece'' is a standard genre label.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Niandai", "rationale": "The transliterated Chinese term, unlikely to be understood without context but presented as an option.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "7bebde2708144371a3f4b9700c46a755", "candidates": [{"name": "Flight", "rationale": "A direct and literary translation of ''逃亡'', implying escape and pursuit.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "On the Run", "rationale": "A very common and evocative English phrase describing a state of逃亡, used in many thriller and crime narratives.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}, {"name": "Taowang", "rationale": "The transliterated term, primarily for stylistic or academic use.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}]}, {"entity_id": "8ca16755840b4a8881ff9faa43ffd4a0", "candidates": [{"name": "Wang Mazi (born Wang Youfu)", "rationale": "Standard transliteration of the nickname and real name, preserving the original character identity and the informative structure.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}, {"name": "Pockmarked Wang (born Wang Youfu)", "rationale": "Translates the descriptive nickname ''Mazi'' (''pockmarked'') which is a common archetype in stories, paired with the transliterated real name.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "Willy Wang (born William Youfu)", "rationale": "Adapts the name to common English nicknaming conventions (''Willy'' for informality, akin to ''Mazi'') and provides anglicized versions (''William'') for the formal name, making it feel native to an English-language story.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}]}, {"entity_id": "bb99d3ad26814961aa211fd6040527bf", "candidates": [{"name": "Li Xiuying", "rationale": "Standard pinyin transliteration, preserving the character''s Chinese identity.", "naming_policy": "transliteration"}, {"name": "Elegant Li", "rationale": "Translates the meaning of the name ''Xiuying'' (''Elegant Heroine/Flower''), which could be used as a descriptive epithet or in a stylized context.", "naming_policy": "literal"}, {"name": "Rosalind Li", "rationale": "Provides an English given name (''Rosalind'') that carries connotations of beauty and grace, similar to ''Xiuying'', while keeping the Chinese surname ''Li'' for heritage. This integrates the character into a Western context.", "naming_policy": "cultural_equivalent"}]}]}', '{
