    "translated_text": "In his left hand, he carried a bulging {{PROP:14c18eb154_14c18e}}, while his right hand tightly gripped the wrist of the woman beside him."
  },
  {
    "id": "e06b5faeca2d45f1bc9f92d4945cb540",
    "translated_text": "**{{CHAR:bb99d3ad26_bb99d3}}** (Wang Mazi''s wife) was dragged along, stumbling. She was seven or eight years younger than Wang Mazi, with delicate yet haggard features; the fine wrinkles at the corners of her eyes were especially pronounced in the shadows. She was wrapped in a somewhat worn, floral-patterned cotton-padded jacket, her hair hastily tied up with a wooden hairpin, a few stray strands stuck to her temples with sweat. She kept looking back, her lips pressed together until they were pale, her other hand unconsciously protecting her lower abdomen—which was slightly rounded, showing a pregnancy of about four or five months."
  },
