    "translated_text": "He released his wife''s wrist and turned', NULL, NULL, 'provider_c86aa37930fd4a56a1d0cf549a62e2a0', NULL);
INSERT INTO public.skill_runs (id, tenant_id, project_id, trace_id, correlation_id, idempotency_key, version, deleted_at, created_at, updated_at, created_by, updated_by, error_code, error_message, retry_count, skill_id, novel_id, chapter_id, input_hash, input_snapshot, status, output_json, raw_response, token_usage, cost_estimate, model_provider_id, model_name) VALUES ('738f237699ad442fa6993fcbd6efe48b', 'default', 'default', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'v1', NULL, '2026-03-01 11:13:44.082345+00', '2026-03-01 11:14:55.98973+00', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 'translation_run', 'novel_b831875078b348ffa5569429fdb4105c', 'chapter_904bae811e7e4e2c9a124bdb12f65be6', '52a1125e2092b3da7cd5995ed23a5bd9', '{"project_id": "ada3637a24de44db91c1359958e586a5", "block_count": 29, "target_language": "en-US"}', 'succeeded', '{"results": [{"id": "c20f6ec8654342f6a3918e9581d6eab7", "translated_text": "# Wang Mazi Returns to the Village"}, {"id": "5dc3c1e66d354f73ad86c007efea076c", "translated_text": "## Scene One: The Old Locust Tree at the Village Entrance"}, {"id": "6bfe63396ef544a49369d2f20d6eec0a", "translated_text": "**Time**: Late at night, around the third watch (approximately 11:45 PM)  \n**Location**: Out by the county line oak  \n**Weather**: A north wind howls, dark clouds obscure the moon, occasional sparse raindrops fall"}, {"id": "a5c96dcf985d4a4697a92513f41d37a6", "translated_text": "---"}, {"id": "9546c8d7a3d04c1c95cdd0ea1cabd7d0", "translated_text": "### 【Environmental Description】"}, {"id": "487b64be1b44437ab2e8568f8243088f", "translated_text": "The century-old locust tree at the village entrance claws at the night wind, its withered branches swaying like ghostly hands, casting fragmented, wavering shadows. Faded remnants of Spring Festival couplets pasted on the tree trunk rustle loudly in the wind, like someone whispering in a low voice. The dirt road leading into the village is pitted and uneven; puddles reflect not a single glimmer of starlight. Only the faint, yellowish glow of oil lamps seeps through the window lattices of a few scattered households in the distance, trembling in the ink-black night."}, {"id": "f10a338f3f424d0f989d42ed743d2da2", "translated_text": "The north wind whirls dust and dead leaves; the air is thick with the damp smell of earth and a faint, distant odor of livestock pens. Further away, the dark outlines of the mountains crouch like giant beasts, silently watching over this village whose peace is about to be shattered."}, {"id": "7457436bd4904ee986e62fd902c0e2a1", "translated_text": "---"}, {"id": "0f44c0eb452c492ba6832ec4de69220b", "translated_text": "### 【Character Entrance】"}, {"id": "aed22a6572f14d06b8c435f2cf069173", "translated_text": "**Wang Mazi** (real name Mason Weaver) approaches from the end of the dirt road, his steps heavy and hurried. He appears to be in his early forties, tall and lean with a slightly hunched back, wearing a faded navy-blue cotton-padded jacket with frayed cuffs. The pockmarks on his face are indistinct in the dim light, but his eyes are unusually bright—the kind of gaze belonging to someone long accustomed to traveling and worldly affairs, yet now mixed with weariness, anxiety, and a trace of barely perceptible wariness."}, {"id": "43f7ad81d8914fe3a18b2efaf71e8fa0", "translated_text": "In his left hand, he carried a bulging The bedroll, while his right hand tightly gripped the wrist of the woman beside him."}, {"id": "157dc29738a54808babe82aa14540b3b", "translated_text": "**Molly** (Wang Mazi''s wife) stumbled along, dragged by him. She was seven or eight years younger than Wang Mazi, with delicate yet haggard features; the fine wrinkles at the corners of her eyes were particularly pronounced in the shadows. She was wrapped in a somewhat worn floral-patterned cotton-padded jacket, her hair hastily pinned up with a wooden hairpin, a few stray strands stuck to her temples with sweat. She kept looking back, her lips pressed together until they turned pale, her other hand unconsciously protecting her lower abdomen—which was slightly rounded, showing a pregnancy of about four or five months."}, {"id": "1dbfd840eaf843058c00f375932fa6a1", "translated_text": "---"}, {"id": "b3c1313dc6b2481ba0ce6fa31297c8f3", "translated_text": "### 【Action and Emotional Details】"}, {"id": "e3cfbae8b54e41e180db6edb94197fa0", "translated_text": "**Wang Mazi**''s footsteps came to an abrupt halt beneath the locust tree."}, {"id": "afaa3fff0f3f4da2ae40f66113d80d34", "translated_text": "He released his wife''s wrist and turned to look back the way they had come. The dirt road stretched empty into the distance, with only the wind''s mournful howl. Yet he squinted and stared for a long time, his Adam''s apple bobbing up and down as if confirming something. Sweat trickled down his temples, leaving a damp trail on his cheekbones."}, {"id": "99549f67bf1145818db3071cfc58f23d", "translated_text": "\"No one''s following,\" he said in a low voice, more to convince himself. His voice was hoarse, parched from the long journey."}, {"id": "77c14fc75d4942c6a278b04392e69837", "translated_text": "**Molly** leaned against the locust tree''s rough trunk, panting, her chest heaving. She raised a hand to wipe her face, unsure if it was rain or tears."}, {"id": "1e9919a065904e7ab39869c84a03d46b", "translated_text": "\"Youfu…\" her voice trembled, \"do we have to come back now? Can''t we wait until daybreak to enter the village?\""}, {"id": "2fb4ceb1c0254eb28367404d59254c32", "translated_text": "Wang Mazi didn''t answer immediately. He crouched down, rummaged in the bundle, and pulled out an oil-paper package containing half a stiff, hard pancake. He broke off a small piece and handed it to his wife, then gnawed on an even smaller piece himself, chewing slowly, his eyes never leaving the road leading into the village."}, {"id": "2378484f012548dcbe21ef4700f469e0", "translated_text": "\"We can''t wait till dawn.\" He finally spoke, crumbs falling from the corner of his mouth. \"Those people in the city... if they find the ledger is missing, this is the first place they''ll come looking.\""}, {"id": "f1cee4e9ee334a479fea130eb5eea1e4", "translated_text": "\"But the villagers...\" Molly took the pancake but didn''t eat it, her fingers unconsciously pinching its edge. \"What if they ask about all these years...\""}, {"id": "aaee57863cd742d5a0ec94d5837d9c9c", "translated_text": "\"Just say we ran a small business in the provincial capital and lost it all.\" Wang Mazi cut her off, his tone resolute. He stood up, patted the dirt off his trouser legs, his movements carrying a fierce determination. \"Remember, Xiuying, we know nothing. Not a single word about the ledger.\""}, {"id": "1b901d7cd7c648f39d6fff11a589cf90", "translated_text": "Molly lowered her head, her fingers moving to her lower abdomen, gently stroking it. Wang Mazi saw this gesture; his eyes softened for an instant, but then hardened again."}, {"id": "ad00b05feace4b10bcee6cf20ff87174", "translated_text": "\"For the child.\" He added in a lowered voice. \"He must be born in a clean place.\""}, {"id": "924448c418d14ca0ad545096e002d651", "translated_text": "---"}, {"id": "52e105366a1d41e8a5ea40af209244b4", "translated_text": "### 【Conflict Foreshadowing】"}, {"id": "a2156e297c924bbfb4f49f71348551ff", "translated_text": "At that very moment, the sound of barking dogs came from the distance."}, {"id": "6060a93e1e144493b5cd4be31cf47af1", "translated_text": "Not just one, but one after another, starting from the east end of the village and spreading through the night like ripples. Wang Mazi stiffened all over, abruptly pulling his wife into the shadow of the locust tree."}], "warnings": 0, "translated": 29}', '```json
